oup with historic vulnerability to incest stereotype as well as contemporary white privilege, Unsettling demonstrates how white Jewish men accused of incest, and even those who defiantly confess it, became improbably sympathetic figures representing supposed white male vulnerability.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aIncest in mass media. 0aIncest in popular culturezUnited States. 0aJews in mass media. 0aJews in popular culturezUnited States. 0aMass mediazUnited States. 0aRacism in mass media. 0aStereotypes (Social psychology) in mass media. 0aWhite peoplexRace identityzUnited States. 0aWhitesxRace identityzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aJews, Whiteness, Incest, Popular culture, Cultural Studies, Celebrities, Community, Politics, Representation, Antisemitism, TV, Film, Literature, Stereotypes, Second-wave Feminism, Masculinity, Nonwhite, Sigmund Freud, Media Studies, White Privilege, Feminism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073913840uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197880727340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978807273423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978807273/original  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-073913-8  Rutgers 